        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">
          <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2">
            <path d="M3 7v10a2 2 0 002 2h14a2 2 0 002-2V9a2 2 0 00-2-2h-6l-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2z"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-title">Telegram Storage</div>
        <p class="feature-description">Unlimited file storage via Telegram integration with CDN delivery.</p>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          <li>Unlimited storage</li>
          <li>Global CDN</li>
          <li>Multiple file types</li>
          <li>Auto-generated URLs</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">
          <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2">
            <path d="M9 3v2m6-2v2M9 19v2m6-2v2M5 9H3m2 6H5m14 0h2m-2 6h2M9 3l6 6m-6 0L3 9m6 3v6m0-6v-6"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-title">MCP Server</div>
        <p class="feature-description">Model Context Protocol for seamless AI/IDE integration with your backend.</p>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          <li>Claude Desktop support</li>
          <li>ChatGPT integration</li>
          <li>Database query tools</li>
          <li>Auth & storage tools</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Services Section -->
  <section id="services" class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2 class="section-title">Services</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">Comprehensive backend services, all connected through one API key.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Database Service -->
    <div class="service-detail">
      <div class="service-detail-header">
        <div class="service-detail-icon">
          <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2">
            <ellipse cx="12" cy="5" rx="3"/>
            <path d="M21 12c0 1.66-1.34 3-3 3s-3-1.34-3-3m0 0c-1.66 0-3 1.34-3 3s1.34 3 3 3m0-6c-1.66 0-3 1.34-3 3s1.34 3 3 3m0 6c-1.66 0-3 1.34-3 3s1.34 3 3 3"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="service-detail-title">Database Service</div>
          <p class="service-detail-description">PostgreSQL with auto-generated REST & GraphQL APIs, plus Row-Level Security for multi-tenant isolation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tabs">
        <button class="tab active" data-tab="db-overview" onclick="switchTab('db-overview', 'services')">Overview</button>
        <button class="tab" data-tab="db-usage" onclick="switchTab('db-usage', 'services')">Usage Examples</button>
      </div>

      <div id="db-overview" class="tab-content active">
        <h3 style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px;">Capabilities</h3>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          <li><strong>Auto REST API</strong> - PostgREST generates RESTful endpoints from your database schema</li>
          <li><strong>GraphQL API</strong> - Postgraphile provides type-safe GraphQL with auto-generated queries</li>
          <li><strong>Row-Level Security</strong> - Multi-tenant data isolation at database level</li>
          <li><strong>Real-time Subscriptions</strong> - Listen to database changes via WebSocket</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; margin: 24px 0 16px;">SDK Installation</h3>
        <div class="code-block">
          <pre><code><span class="comment"># Install from GitHub</span>
npm install https://github.com/Mkid095/nextmavens-js.git

<span class="comment"># Or add to package.json</span>
{
  "dependencies": {
    "nextmavens-js": "github:Mkid095/nextmavens-js"
  }
}</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="db-usage" class="tab-content">
        <h3 style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px;">JavaScript SDK Usage</h3>
        <div class="code-block">
          <pre><code><span class="keyword">import</span> { NextMavensClient } <span class="keyword">from</span> <span class="string">'nextmavens-js'</span>;

<span class="keyword">const</span> client = <span class="keyword">new</span> NextMavensClient({
  apiKey: <span class="string">'nm_live_pk_your_key_here'</span>
});

<span class="comment">// Query users</span>
<span class="keyword">const</span> users = <span class="keyword">await</span> client.database
  .from(<span class="string">'users'</span>)
  .select(<span class="string">'id'</span>, <span class="string">'email'</span>, <span class="string">'name'</span>)
  .eq(<span class="string">'tenant_id'</span>, tenantId)
  .execute();

<span class="comment">// Insert data</span>
<span class="keyword">await</span> client.database.insert(<span class="string">'posts'</span>, {
  title: <span class="string">'Hello World'</span>,
  user_id: 123
});</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Auth Service -->
    <div class="service-detail">
      <div class="service-detail-header">
        <div class="service-detail-icon">
          <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2">
            <path d="M9 12.75L11.25 15 15 9.75m-3-7.036A11.959 11.959 0 013.598 6 11.99 11.99 0 003 9.749c0 5.592 3.824 10.29 9 11.623 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.31-.21-2.571-.598-3.751h-.152c-3.196 0-6.1-1.248-8.25-3.285z"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="service-detail-title">Authentication Service</div>
          <p class="service-detail-description">Complete authentication system with JWT tokens, user management, and secure password handling.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tabs">
        <button class="tab active" data-tab="auth-overview" onclick="switchTab('auth-overview', 'services')">Overview</button>
        <button class="tab" data-tab="auth-usage" onclick="switchTab('auth-usage', 'services')">Usage Examples</button>
      </div>

      <div id="auth-overview" class="tab-content active">
        <h3 style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px;">Features</h3>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          <li><strong>JWT Authentication</strong> - Stateless tokens with configurable expiration</li>
          <li><strong>User Registration</strong> - Email/password signup with validation</li>
          <li><strong>Password Reset</strong> - Secure reset flows via email</li>
          <li><strong>Profile Management</strong> - Update user information</li>
          <li><strong>Refresh Tokens</strong> - Automatic token refresh without re-authentication</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; margin: 24px 0 16px;">Endpoints</h3>
        <div class="endpoint-list">
          <div class="endpoint-item">
            <div class="endpoint-label">Login</div>
            <div class="endpoint-value">POST https://auth.nextmavens.cloud/api/auth/login</div>
          </div>
          <div class="endpoint-item">
            <div class="endpoint-label">Signup</div>
            <div class="endpoint-value">POST https://auth.nextmavens.cloud/api/auth/signup</div>
          </div>
          <div class="endpoint-item">
            <div class="endpoint-label">Refresh Token</div>
            <div class="endpoint-value">POST https://auth.nextmavens.cloud/api/auth/refresh</div>
          </div>
          <div class="endpoint-item">
            <div class="endpoint-label">Get Current User</div>
            <div class="endpoint-value">GET https://auth.nextmavens.cloud/api/auth/me</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="auth-usage" class="tab-content">
        <h3 style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px;">Authentication Usage</h3>
        <div class="code-block">
          <pre><code><span class="keyword">import</span> { NextMavensClient } <span class="keyword">from</span> <span class="string">'nextmavens-js'</span>;

<span class="keyword">const</span> client = <span class="keyword">new</span> NextMavensClient({
  apiKey: <span class="string">'nm_live_pk_your_key_here'</span>
});

<span class="comment">// Sign up new user</span>
<span class="keyword">const</span> { user } = <span class="keyword">await</span> client.auth.signUp({
  email: <span class="string">'user@example.com'</span>,
  password: <span class="string">'secure_password'</span>,
  name: <span class="string">'John Doe'</span>,
  tenantId: <span class="string">'your-tenant-id'</span>
});

<span class="comment">// Sign in existing user</span>
<span class="keyword">const</span> { user, accessToken } = <span class="keyword">await</span> client.auth.signIn({
  email: <span class="string">'user@example.com'</span>,
  password: <span class="string">'secure_password'</span>
});

<span class="comment">// Get current user from server</span>
<span class="keyword">const</span> currentUser = <span class="keyword">await</span> client.auth.getCurrentUser();

<span class="comment">// Update password</span>
<span class="keyword">await</span> client.auth.changePassword(<span class="string">'oldPassword'</span>, <span class="string">'newPassword'</span>);</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Realtime Service -->
    <div class="service-detail">
      <div class="service-detail-header">
        <div class="service-detail-icon">
          <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2">
            <path d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="service-detail-title">Realtime Service</div>
          <p class="service-detail-description">WebSocket-based real-time data sync with automatic reconnection and row-level filtering.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; margin: 24px 0 16px;">Features</h3>
      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li><strong>WebSocket Protocol</strong> - Efficient bidirectional communication</li>
        <li><strong>PostgreSQL LISTEN/NOTIFY</strong> - Database-driven notifications</li>
        <li><strong>Per-table Subscriptions</strong> - Subscribe to specific tables</li>
        <li><strong>Row-level Filtering</strong> - Only get updates for specific rows</li>
        <li><strong>Auto Reconnection</strong> - Automatically reconnect on disconnect</li>
        <li><strong>Event Types</strong> - INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE events</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; margin: 24px 0 16px;">WebSocket Endpoint</h3>
      <div class="endpoint-list">
        <div class="endpoint-item">
          <div class="endpoint-label">WebSocket URL</div>
          <div class="endpoint-value">wss://realtime.nextmavens.cloud</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; margin: 24px 0 16px;">Realtime Usage</h3>
      <div class="code-block">
        <pre><code><span class="keyword">import</span> { NextMavensClient } <span class="keyword">from</span> <span class="string">'nextmavens-js'</span>;

<span class="keyword">const</span> client = <span class="keyword">new</span> NextMavensClient({
  apiKey: <span class="string">'nm_live_pk_your_key_here'</span>
});

<span class="comment">// Connect to realtime</span>
client.realtime.connect();

<span class="comment">// Subscribe to all changes on a table</span>
<span class="keyword">const</span> unsubscribe = client.realtime.onInsert(<span class="string">'users'</span>, (payload) => {
  console.log(<span class="string">'New user:'</span>, payload.data);
});

<span class="comment">// Subscribe to updates only</span>
client.realtime.onUpdate(<span class="string">'posts'</span>, (payload) => {
  console.log(<span class="string">'Post updated:'</span>, payload);
});

<span class="comment">// Subscribe to specific row</span>
<span class="keyword">const</span> unsub = client.realtime.subscribeToRow(<span class="string">'posts'</span>, postId, (payload) => {
  console.log(<span class="string">'Your post updated:'</span>, payload);
});

<span class="comment">// Unsubscribe when done</span>
unsubscribe();</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Storage Service -->
    <div class="service-detail">
      <div class="service-detail-header">
        <div class="service-detail-icon">
          <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2">
            <path d="M3 7v10a2 2 0 002 2h14a2 2 0 002-2V9a2 2 0 00-2-2h-6l-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2z"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="service-detail-title">Storage Service</div>
          <p class="service-detail-description">Telegram-based file storage with unlimited capacity and global CDN delivery.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; margin: 24px 0 16px;">Features</h3>
      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li><strong>Unlimited Storage</strong> - No storage limits, pay only for bandwidth</li>
        <li><strong>Global CDN</strong> - Files delivered from edge locations worldwide</li>
        <li><strong>Multiple File Types</strong> - Images, documents, videos, audio, and more</li>
        <li><strong>Auto-generated URLs</strong> - Get download URLs instantly</li>
        <li><strong>File Management</strong> - List, get info, and delete files</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; margin:  24px 0 16px;">How It Works</h3>
      <div class="service-detail">
        <ol style="padding-left: 20px; color: var(--slate-600);">
          <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Send files to <strong>@nextmavensuploadsbot</strong> on Telegram</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Receive a <strong>File ID</strong> for each uploaded file</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Use the File ID to get file info and download URLs</li>
          <li>Store the File ID in your database alongside your records</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <h3 style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; margin: 24px 0 16px;">Storage Usage</h3>
      <div class="code-block">
        <pre><code><span class="keyword">import</span> { NextMavensClient } <span class="keyword">from</span> <span class="string">'nextmavens-js'</span>;

<span class="keyword">const</span> client = <span class="keyword">new</span> NextMavensClient({
  apiKey: <span class="string">'nm_live_pk_your_key_here'</span>
});

<span class="comment">// Get file information</span>
<span class="keyword">const</span> file = <span class="keyword">await</span> client.storage.getFileInfo(<span class="string">'telegram-file-id'</span>);

<span class="comment">// Get download URL</span>
<span class="keyword">const</span> url = <span class="keyword">await</span> client.storage.getDownloadUrl(<span class="string">'telegram-file-id'</span>);

<span class="comment">// List files with filters</span>
<span class="keyword">const</span> { files } = <span class="keyword">await</span> client.storage.listFiles({
  file_type: <span class="string">'photo'</span>,
  limit: <span class="number">20</span>
});

<span class="comment">// Get storage statistics</span>
<span class="keyword">const</span> stats = <span class="keyword">await</span> client.storage.getStats({ tenantId });</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MCP & AI Section -->
  <section id="mcp" class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2 class="section-title">MCP Server & AI Integration</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">Connect your backend to AI assistants with Model Context Protocol. Full support for Claude Desktop, ChatGPT, and more.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mcp-integration">
      <div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 40px;">
        <h2 style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; color: white; margin-bottom: 12px;">AI-Native Backend Development</h2>
        <p style="font-size: 18px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);">Let Claude or ChatGPT write queries, manage data, and deploy your backend naturally through conversation.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mcp-grid">
        <div class="mcp-card">
          <h3>ü§ñ What is MCP?</h3>
          <p>The Model Context Protocol (MCP) is an open standard that allows AI assistants to seamlessly connect to external tools and data sources. Think of it as a universal plug-in system for AI.</p>

          <h3 style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; margin: 24px 0 12px; color: white;">Why Use NextMavens MCP?</h3>
          <ul class="mcp-tools">
            <li>Query databases with natural language</li>
            <li>Create and manage users through chat</li>
            <li>Upload and manage files via AI</li>
            <li>Inspect schema and get context</li>
            <li>Full database, auth, and storage tools</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mcp-card">
          <h3>üöÄ Quick Start</h3>
          <p>Install the NextMavens MCP server and connect it to your AI assistant.</p>

          <h4 style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: white; margin: 20px 0 8px;">1. Install via npm</h4>
          <div style="background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3); border-radius: 12px; padding: 16px; margin: 12px 0;">
            <code style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--emerald-300);">
              npm install https://github.com/Mkid095/nextmavens-mcp-server
            </code>
          </div>

          <h4 style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: white; margin: 20px 0 8px;">2. Get Your API Key</h4>
          <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); font-size: 13px; margin-bottom: 12px;">Sign up at <a href="https://portal.nextmavens.cloud" style="color: var(--emerald-400);">portal.nextmavens.cloud</a> to get your free API key.</p>

          <h4 style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: white; margin: 20px 0 8px;">3. Configure Claude Desktop</h4>
          <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px; font-size: 13px;">Edit your Claude config at:</p>
          <div style="background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3); border-radius: 12px; padding: 12px; font-size: 12px; margin-bottom: 12px;">
            <code style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);">~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json</code>
          </div>
          <div style="background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3); border-radius: 12px; padding: 16px; font-size: 12px;">
            <pre style="color: var(--emerald-300); margin: 0;"><code>{
  "mcpServers": {
    "nextmavens": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/path/to/nextmavens-mcp-server/dist/index.js"],
      "env": {
        "NEXTMAVENS_API_KEY": "nm_live_pk_your_key_here"
      }
    }
  }
}</code></pre>
          </div>

          <h4 style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: white; margin: 20px 0 8px;">4. Configure ChatGPT (Optional)</h4>
          <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px; font-size: 13px;">For ChatGPT, add this to your ChatGPT config:</p>
          <div style="background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3); border-radius: 12px; padding: 16px; font-size: 12px;">
            <pre style="color: var(--emerald-300); margin: 0;"><code>{
  "mcpServers": {
    "nextmavens": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/path/to/nextmavens-mcp-server/dist/index.js"],
      "env": {
        "NEXTMAVENS_API_KEY": "nm_live_pk_your_key_here"
      }
    }
  }
}</code></pre>
          </div>

          <h4 style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: white; margin: 20px 0 8px;">5. Restart & Start Chatting</h4>
          <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); font-size: 13px;">Restart Claude Desktop or ChatGPT. You'll now see NextMavens tools available in your conversations!</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 40px auto;">
        <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--slate-900); margin-bottom: 24px;">Available MCP Tools</h3>

        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 16px;">
          <div style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px;">
            <h4 style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px;">üóÑÔ∏è Database Tools</h4>
            <ul style="list-style: none; font-size: 14px; color: var(--slate-600);">
              <li style="margin-bottom: 6px;"><code style="font-size: 12px; background: var(--slate-100); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px;">nextmavens_query</code> - Query data with filters</li>
              <li style="margin-bottom: 6px;"><code style="font-size: 12px; background: var(--slate-100); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px;">nextmavens_insert</code> - Insert new rows</li>
              <li style="margin-bottom: 6px;"><code style="font-size: 12px; background: var(--slate-100); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px;">nextmavens_update</code> - Update records</li>
              <li style="margin-bottom: 6px;"><code style="font-size: 12px; background: var(--slate-100); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px;">nextmavens_delete</code> - Delete rows</li>
              <li><code style="font-size: 12px; background: var(--slate-100); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px;">nextmavens_tables</code> - List all tables</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px;">
            <h4 style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px;">üîê Auth Tools</h4>
            <ul style="list-style: none; font-size: 14px; color: var(--slate-600);">
              <li style="margin-bottom: 6px;"><code style="font-size: 12px; background: var(--slate-100); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px;">nextmavens_signin</code> - User login</li>
              <li style="margin-bottom: 6px;"><code style="font-size: 12px; background: var(--slate-100); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px;">nextmavens_signup</code> - Create users</li>
              <li><code style="font-size: 12px; background: var(--slate-100); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px;">nextmavens_get_user</code> - Get user info</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px;">
            <h4 style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px;">üìÅ Storage Tools</h4>
            <ul style="list-style: none; font-size: 14px; color: var(--slate-600);">
              <li style="margin-bottom: 6px;"><code style="font-size: 12px; background: var(--slate-100); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px;">nextmavens_file_info</code> - Get file info</li>
              <li style="margin-bottom: 6px;"><code style="font-size: 12px; background: var(--slate-100); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px;">nextmavens_file_download_url</code> - Get download URLs</li>
              <li style="margin-bottom: 6px;"><code style="font-size: 12px; background: var(--slate-100); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px;">nextmavens_list_files</code> - List files</li>
              <li><code style="font-size: 12px; background: var(--slate-100); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px;">nextmavens_storage_stats</code> - Get storage stats</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px;">
            <h4 style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px;">üîç GraphQL Tools</h4>
            <ul style="list-style: none; font-size: 14px; color: var(--slate-600);">
              <li style="margin-bottom: 6px;"><code style="font-size: 12px; background: var(--slate-100); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px;">nextmavens_graphql</code> - Run GraphQL queries</li>
              <li><code style="font-size: 12px; background: var(--slate-100); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px;">nextmavens_graphql_introspect</code> - Get schema info</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
